metadata.name: Botanical Gardens #31
metadata.description:
Question shouldn't be, What is Art?
Just because the answer is quite simple, imagination and creation to inspire.
The question should be, What is Art without dimensions, colors, shades, inspiration, creativity, vibrancy, variations, etc... "NOTHING", we get above all from God's Creation(Art) and no man can ever be a bigger artist than God. 

I always had attraction towards the flowers, the colors, the creativity, the fragrance, all have enticed me to appreciate what we are blessed with.

Botanical Gardens is all about dimensions, colors, vibrancy, and variations.
In this project we go deep with sin & cos to generate patterns of flowers, in comes the Botany's premium color themes range which cover from fade to vibrant colors. Add with some onclick variations, you can always find the best possible locations for your flowers and save.

This project is token of my appreciation to God for blessing us all, with this amazing art surrounding us.

Click on NFT to see the flower dance.
Press "S" to save 1000x1000 png of your mint.
You are welcome to request a Hi-Res image for your holdings via twitter @TheRealBotany

metadata.name: Balanced #43
Alleles #279
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Evaluation of the information extracted from the provided genetic information suggests subject may have a disposition tending towards infrequent periods of jealousy and egocentricity, yet also has the potential to display a high degree of creativity and kindness. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 123-132cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 89-93 years. Presence of mutation may require supervised observation to determine the presence of any superhuman abilities. It is advised that special attention be paid to markers 218 through 438, as these may indicate the presence of pyrokinesis and or accelerated cellular regeneration.

metadata.name: Balanced #280
NO ROADMAP #57
metadata.description:
This collection represents the need we have to move forward despite the obstacles that the road may present us.
We identify ourselves with the one who, even without the most optimal conditions, continues on its way until the goal is reached
Web 3.0 is a space that appears to us without a roadmap, so that everyone can explore it and learn.
Even though we only get to have a skateboard, in this journey of work and effort, we will continue asking ourselves until we can at last get it
WEN LAMBO?

+ 100 Roaders + Color variations
+ 50 Backgrounds + Color variations
+ 30 Foreground
+ 50 Animals
+ 25 Foreground elements
+ 10 Police cars on fire

metadata.name: Disjoint and Disoriented #80
metadata.description:
Disjoint and Disoriented is about the abstract structure formed by the equalities and oppositions of its parts.

It might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop is recommended.

There are three render options available as url parameters in live mode:
- size=XXXX (up to 5760 pixels)
- texture=0 (disable canvas texture for print)
- shader=1 (use the shader throughout the painting process, can be heavy)

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi and lunarean, 2022.

metadata.name: =DMT= #341
metadata.description:
The Spirit Molecule, an experience out of this world, available in this world.

What will you see when you take your =DMT=? I wish you a great trip.

Groups of color palettes, lines and bezier curves combine to create what sometimes looks like a sun, an eye, a flower, an explosion, a pair of wings or a combination of these.

I hope in the future Psychedelics will be accessible to people in controlled settings with professional care and support. 
The Ayahuasca ceremonies happening around the world are a good step in this direction.

Press 's' to save a 3000x3000 px PNG.

Created by UpOnlyFan in August 2022 with p5js.

@(=_=)- @brainspinky2014 ¬(=_=)7

metadata.name: contrapuntos #148
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.
